1:1 COMMENT "# io_lstat.z -- inspect a path with `io.lstat`, which does NOT"
1:63 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# follow symlinks."
2:19 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# `stat(2)` follows symlinks and reports the target; `lstat(2)`"
4:64 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# reports the link itself, so `kind` can be `symlink`. `filestat`"
5:66 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# also carries `mtime_seconds` (Unix epoch seconds; a typed `time`"
6:67 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# will replace this in a follow-up) and `mode` (raw POSIX mode bits:"
7:69 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# file type + permission bits, as from `stat(2)`)."
8:51 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "#"
9:2 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# This example stats `/tmp` (usually a directory, not a symlink) and"
10:69 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# prints the three richer fields. Inside the narrowed `case ok then`"
11:69 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# arm, `s.kind` / `s.size` / `s.mtime_seconds` read directly through"
12:69 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# the payload."
13:15 EOL "\n"
14:1 EOL "\n"
